Model

Class Game

  • java.lang.Object
    • Model.Game

  • public class Game
extends java.lang.Object
    The class that implements the finite automata, that is the base of game process. Also, handles competition, false start and most part of other game process aspects. Implemented as singleton.

      • proceed

        public static void proceed()
                    throws GameException,
                           java.lang.InterruptedException
        Function for transferring the FA to the next state. Before calling this method it is needed to set Game.state to the desired state.
        Throws:
        GameException - in case of an attempt of transition, that is not valid for this automata
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • recieveApplication

        public static void recieveApplication(Player from)
        Receive applying from the player, who wishes to take part in competition for answer. After applying the user is processed according the game rules and current context of the game.
        Parameters:
        from - the player entity, associated with the applied user of player application
